meanwhile a government source said moslem rebels had pushed 
back government troops in heavy fighting near the southeastern city 
of khost he said the usbacked rebels had taken several military 
posts on the outskirts of the town 
fierce fighting and heavy rebel artillery also has forced the 
closing of the khost airport which was being used to supply the 
government troops he said a government convoy of more than 200 
trucks headed toward khost with ammunition weapons and other 
supplies was attacked before it could reach the city according to 
the source who spoke on condition of anonymity 
rebels have been fighting the sovietbacked government 11 years 
to set up an islamic republic in afghanistan 
they have been trying since the summer to khost the offensive 
followed the rebels failure to seize the eastern city of 
jalalabad which they had hoped to use as a base for operations 
inside afghanistan 
khost is 25 miles from the pakistan border where the rebels are 
based 
in kabul a rocket slammed into the dining hall of the guzagur 
textile mill at 1145 am said gulam haida the factory manager 
workers were eating lunch when the rocket pierced the corrugated 
tin roof and sprayed shrapnel around the room two men and three 
women were killed immediately and another 26 people were rushed to 
hospitals said haida all of the people in the room were either 
injured or killed he said 
how could anyone escape he said it happened like 
lightning 
at dusk the dining room was in shambles pieces of roof and 
ceiling hung from wood rafters tables and chairs lay in disarray 
blood stained the packed dirt floor 
we are all poor people we dont want any more rockets said 
shaida roh who has worked at the factory 23 years 
more than 350 people have been killed and 800 injured since june 
in frequent rocket attacks on kabul the government blames the 
rebels for the attacks but the rebels say the government is 
rocketing its own people to make the guerrillas look bad 
for the last four days rocket attacks on kabuls international 
airport have forced the cancellation of several civilian flights 
officials and diplomats say rocket attacks thursday shut down 
civilian service for several hours 
the government source said intermittent attacks friday and 
saturday also affected the transport of goods into afghanistan from 
the soviet union 
diplomats in pakistan and kabul have said the soviet union is 
undertaking a large airlift of military and food supplies for the 
afghan army 
soviet troops withdrew from afghanistan in february after a 
decadelong intervention in the war 
