president bushs veto saturday of legislation 
allowing federally financed abortions for rape and incest victims 
marks the third time since he took office that he has exercised 
that constitutional prerogative 
bush said he vetoed the 1567 billion health education and 
labor spending measure that included the abortion provision because 
he opposed expanding the use of tax dollars for abortion 
current law makes federal medicaid funds for abortion available 
to poor women only when the mothers life is endangered 
this summer the president vetoed a bill that effectively would 
have killed a joint production agreement between the united states 
and japan for the fsx jet fighter 
in june he also vetoed legislation that would have raised the 
minimum wage to 455 an hour by october 1991 
congressional opponents of the fighter deal wanted to place 
