hayes suffered from alzheimers disease and parkinsons disease 
and had been in a nursing home for about four years 
he attended harvard and yale universities and was a rhodes 
scholar in 1933 hayes began working in the bond department of 
national city bank of new york which became citibank 
hayes was appointed to the federal reserve in 1956 and worked 
there until 1975 during the same period he was vice chairman of 
the federal open market committee 
